title: Next Generation Experimental Aircraft Becomes NASA’s Newest X-Plane
summary: NASA and Boeing said Monday the aircraft produced through the agency’s Sustainable Flight Demonstrator project has been designated by the U.S. Air Force as the X-66A.

title: Zero-Error Systems raises $7.5 million
summary: With the new funding, ZES plans to expand in the U.S. market to encourage private space companies to adopt its technology.

title: Space domain awareness provisions in draft NDAA proposal
summary: The House Armed Services Committee’s strategic forces subcommittee is proposing legislation that would require DoD to share threat intelligence with commercial satellite operators.

title: NASA Invites Media to Tours, Opening of Earth Information Center
summary: NASA Administrator Bill Nelson is inviting media to a ribbon cutting ceremony on Wednesday, June 21, for the opening of NASA’s Earth Information Center at the agency’s headquarters in Washington. The exhibit is a hybrid – part physical, part online – effort that blends science and art to allow visitors to see how our planet is changing.
